OL,5, Two fraudsters have been jailed for    
OL,6, their part in a series of scams in     
OL,7, which 245 people lost millions of      
OL,8, pounds in pension savings.             
OL,10,FAlan Barratt, 62, and Susan Dalton, 66,
OL,11,Ftricked people into transferring       
OL,12,Fsavings to schemes supposedly investing
OL,13,Fin property or "truffle trees".        
OL,15,FOne victim told the BBC that the       
OL,16,Ffraudsters had wanted to secure their  
OL,17,Fown pension "by taking mine instead".  
OL,19,FBarratt and Dalton admitted fraud based
OL,20,Fon their roles as pension trustees.    
